snippet.textDisplay: She was a lot prettier before all the surgery. In that picture she's had a buccal fat removal done, but that was a good choice because it made her the beauty she was on The Rum Diary. Before that her face was a bit too average for Hollywood, if you look at her on Pineapple Express she looks chubby, coz she had naturally rounder face. After the buccal fat was removed, her facial structure "came out" and her cheekbones looked more prominent and her lower face was more "feminine" and smaller.. Then she propably got carried away with the plastic surgery and had nose jobs (which were very nicely done, very subtle), then upper lip lift which was completely unnecessary and if you watch some of her interviews now, you can see that her upper lip moves strangely when she speaks, so she might have suffered from some nerve damage in that procedure.. But the biggest faux pas was those horrible cheek implants! Not everyone looks good with high prominent cheek bones🤦🏻 like you said, more natural is prettier, she's changing, or has already changed her entire face! And that's never a good look! By all means do little operations that enhance your own beauty but don't change your whole face! She was veery very pretty when she was with Johnny but after that she's changed a whole lot! Her face looks puffy now, idk if it's just the weight gain and her preference of lifestyle (drinking alcohol, not having enough sleep, definitely doing a lot of drugs etc.) or has she had some filler or fat injected in her face to cover up, or rather soften those huge cheek implants that looked like lady Gaga as a "born this way" monster when AH  was still skinny in 2016 or 2017🤔 this is all irrelevant, but it's my take as an aesthetician (I work at a plastic surgeons practice here in Finland, so I'm kind of drawn into "judging" celebrities changing looks😁 sorry, can't help it 🤷🏻btw I need to give credit to Lorry Hill, she did an excellent video on AH's plastic surgeries👍
